  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fostering Gender Equality in and through the Media</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The media are central to shape perceptions, ideas, attitudes and behaviour and should therefore reflect women and men in all their diversity.

UNESCO will continue work in this domain, particularly fostering the application of UNESCO&apos;s Gender-Sensitive Indicators for Media. New resources will be introduced for Field Offices and National Commissions to implement gender transformative action in and through media, such as editorial guidelines for portrayal of men and women, sports broadcasting and treatment of gender-specific concerns.

The Organisation will strengthen capacities of media decision-makers and practitioners, governments and media authorities as well as advocate to hold media to account on gender equality in content. This action targets SDG 5.</narrative>
  </description>
